WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:43.170 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.170 --> 00:00:45.410 align:middle line:84%
>>Nearly 900 years
ago, the Holy Land

00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:48.206 align:middle line:84%
was home to one of the most
extraordinary organizations

00:00:48.206 --> 00:00:49.475 align:middle line:90%
that has ever existed.

00:00:49.475 --> 00:00:53.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:55.340 align:middle line:84%
The Knights of the
Temple of Solomon

00:00:55.340 --> 00:00:59.020 align:middle line:84%
were elite warriors,
unparalleled entrepreneurs,

00:00:59.020 --> 00:01:03.900 align:middle line:84%
and devoted men of God, ready
at any moment to kill and die.

00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:07.513 align:middle line:84%
They had one mission: to
define the Christian Holy Land.

00:01:07.513 --> 00:01:11.460 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:14.680 align:middle line:84%
After a severe mauling by
the legendary Islamic leader

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:17.990 align:middle line:84%
Saladin, the Knights
Templar had mobilized

00:01:17.990 --> 00:01:20.760 align:middle line:84%
their enormous financial
resources in Western Europe.

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:21.790 align:middle line:90%


00:01:21.790 --> 00:01:26.330 align:middle line:84%
Front line defenses had been
reconstructed and garrisoned,

00:01:26.330 --> 00:01:29.730 align:middle line:84%
but how long could the
outnumbered Templars hold out

00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:33.720 align:middle line:84%
against an enemy that had all
the logistical advantages,

00:01:33.720 --> 00:01:37.090 align:middle line:84%
and just how dangerous were
their opponents back in Western

00:01:37.090 --> 00:01:39.690 align:middle line:84%
Europe, envious of
their land and wealth?

00:01:39.690 --> 00:02:03.410 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.410 --> 00:02:06.320 align:middle line:84%
A Knight of the Temple of
Solomon, recruited in Europe

00:02:06.320 --> 00:02:08.639 align:middle line:84%
and sent to the front
line in the Holy Land,

00:02:08.639 --> 00:02:11.980 align:middle line:84%
soon became hardened to
the conditions of the east.

00:02:11.980 --> 00:02:14.320 align:middle line:84%
As monks of the
Catholic Church, they

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:16.860 align:middle line:84%
were well accustomed
to strict discipline,

00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:19.900 align:middle line:84%
and their every moment, awake
and asleep, was regulated.

00:02:19.900 --> 00:02:21.130 align:middle line:90%


00:02:21.130 --> 00:02:24.500 align:middle line:84%
Each day was taken up with
prayer, work, and above all,

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:26.730 align:middle line:90%
constant training for battle.

00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:30.830 align:middle line:84%
There was no leisure time,
and, in fact, most of the time,

00:02:30.830 --> 00:02:32.360 align:middle line:84%
there was not much
battle, either.

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:38.130 align:middle line:90%


00:02:38.130 --> 00:02:41.210 align:middle line:84%
Warfare was expensive
in men and horses,

00:02:41.210 --> 00:02:43.460 align:middle line:84%
and for decades, the
order had generally

00:02:43.460 --> 00:02:45.070 align:middle line:84%
pursued a cautious
policy in the east.

00:02:45.070 --> 00:02:46.340 align:middle line:90%


00:02:46.340 --> 00:02:49.680 align:middle line:84%
This policy had even
included negotiating truces

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:51.840 align:middle line:84%
with local Islamic
leaders, which

00:02:51.840 --> 00:02:54.540 align:middle line:84%
made other Crusaders
deeply uneasy,

00:02:54.540 --> 00:02:57.080 align:middle line:84%
especially when they
negotiated with the leader

00:02:57.080 --> 00:02:59.665 align:middle line:84%
of the Shiite Muslim sect
called the Assassins.

00:02:59.665 --> 00:03:01.100 align:middle line:90%


00:03:01.100 --> 00:03:04.680 align:middle line:84%
The Templars had no qualms in
implementing any policy that

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:07.986 align:middle line:84%
strengthened their
position in the east.

00:03:07.986 --> 00:03:16.180 align:middle line:90%


00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:18.280 align:middle line:10%
>>They're not just
professional soldiers;

00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:20.700 align:middle line:10%
the Templars are the
professional defenders

00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.105 align:middle line:10%
of the frontier, and that's
more than just military.

00:03:23.105 --> 00:03:27.460 align:middle line:84%
It has to be diplomatic, it
has to be political and so on,

00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:31.500 align:middle line:84%
so maybe this is why
the Templars picked

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:35.580 align:middle line:84%
up on the possibility of an
alliance with the Assassins

00:03:35.580 --> 00:03:40.085 align:middle line:84%
more readily than did the
secular rulers of the Crusader

00:03:40.085 --> 00:03:40.585 align:middle line:90%
states.

00:03:40.585 --> 00:03:49.550 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:52.010 align:middle line:84%
>>Pilgrims and Crusaders
visiting the Holy Land

00:03:52.010 --> 00:03:54.420 align:middle line:84%
for the first time were
often angry to discover

00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:56.900 align:middle line:84%
that the resident
Crusaders had negotiated

00:03:56.900 --> 00:03:59.510 align:middle line:90%
a truce with the Muslim enemy.

00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:01.600 align:middle line:84%
They had spent a great
deal of money to get there

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:02.560 align:middle line:90%
and had traveled far.

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:08.930 align:middle line:90%


00:04:08.930 --> 00:04:10.690 align:middle line:84%
Newly arrived
travelers could not

00:04:10.690 --> 00:04:13.476 align:middle line:84%
believe that any Christians,
especially the Templars,

00:04:13.476 --> 00:04:14.600 align:middle line:90%
even talked to the Muslims.

00:04:14.600 --> 00:04:28.440 align:middle line:90%


00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:31.040 align:middle line:84%
>>Fundamentally,
they were intolerant

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:32.260 align:middle line:90%
on an everyday basis.

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:33.750 align:middle line:90%


00:04:33.750 --> 00:04:36.500 align:middle line:84%
For much of the time, they
had to be tolerant-- it's just

00:04:36.500 --> 00:04:40.710 align:middle line:84%
a matter of common sense
and an ability to exist.

00:04:40.710 --> 00:04:41.960 align:middle line:90%
These people are not stupid.

00:04:41.960 --> 00:04:43.510 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:47.390 align:middle line:84%
Their beliefs were intolerant--
much more intolerant

00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:49.460 align:middle line:84%
than ours are
today, but they were

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:51.650 align:middle line:84%
living, as I said,
on a frontier.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:54.290 align:middle line:84%
They had to deal
with their neighbors.

00:04:54.290 --> 00:04:58.300 align:middle line:84%
They were not in a position
to wage perpetual war.

00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:00.680 align:middle line:84%
They knew it, their leaders
knew it, everybody knew it.

00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:04.500 align:middle line:84%
So pragmatism-- I won't say
it was the order of the day,

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:08.180 align:middle line:84%
but they were perfectly willing
and capable of being pragmatic.

00:05:08.180 --> 00:05:09.740 align:middle line:84%
This does not make
them different

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:11.520 align:middle line:90%
to other Medieval people.

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:17.670 align:middle line:10%
>>So there were many day to day
contacts between all the Franks

00:05:17.670 --> 00:05:20.450 align:middle line:10%
in the east, and some of
these are very colorfully

00:05:20.450 --> 00:05:23.660 align:middle line:10%
described by a Damascene
chronicler called

00:05:23.660 --> 00:05:24.910 align:middle line:10%
Usama ibn Munqidh.

00:05:24.910 --> 00:05:26.060 align:middle line:90%


00:05:26.060 --> 00:05:30.280 align:middle line:84%
One of these stories is
the most well known one

00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:33.940 align:middle line:84%
about a Frank newly
arrived from the west, who

00:05:33.940 --> 00:05:40.720 align:middle line:84%
forces Usama to pray facing
east, and one of the Templars

00:05:40.720 --> 00:05:44.560 align:middle line:84%
intervenes, apologizes
to Usama, and says,

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:50.660 align:middle line:84%
no, this man is a newcomer, he
doesn't understand our ways,

00:05:50.660 --> 00:05:53.609 align:middle line:84%
you can pray in
whatever way you wish.

00:05:53.609 --> 00:05:55.150 align:middle line:84%
And this has sometimes
been presented

00:05:55.150 --> 00:05:57.590 align:middle line:84%
as showing that
the Templars were

00:05:57.590 --> 00:05:59.710 align:middle line:84%
very friendly with
the Muslims, but I

00:05:59.710 --> 00:06:04.460 align:middle line:84%
think it really shows much
more, that in daily life,

00:06:04.460 --> 00:06:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Templars and other Franks
had frequent contact

00:06:07.510 --> 00:06:08.360 align:middle line:90%
with the Muslims.

00:06:08.360 --> 00:06:13.440 align:middle line:84%
Many of them spoke Arabic, many
more than has been previously

00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:14.980 align:middle line:90%
said, spoke Arabic, I think.

00:06:14.980 --> 00:06:16.210 align:middle line:90%


00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:20.250 align:middle line:84%
So it was necessary,
in order to exist,

00:06:20.250 --> 00:06:23.000 align:middle line:84%
to have these daily contacts,
but that doesn't necessarily

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.680 align:middle line:84%
affect their commitment
to the Holy War.

00:06:25.680 --> 00:06:33.320 align:middle line:90%


00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:35.730 align:middle line:84%
>>Although the Templars
had, time and time again,

00:06:35.730 --> 00:06:39.220 align:middle line:84%
proved themselves to be
dedicated enemies of Islam,

00:06:39.220 --> 00:06:41.346 align:middle line:84%
there would always
be rumors that they

00:06:41.346 --> 00:06:42.470 align:middle line:90%
fraternized with the enemy.

00:06:42.470 --> 00:06:43.640 align:middle line:90%


00:06:43.640 --> 00:06:45.670 align:middle line:84%
One day, the Templars
would actually

00:06:45.670 --> 00:06:48.970 align:middle line:84%
be accused of secretly
being Muslims themselves.

00:06:48.970 --> 00:07:03.460 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.460 --> 00:07:05.980 align:middle line:84%
By joining the Order of
the Temple of Solomon,

00:07:05.980 --> 00:07:08.440 align:middle line:84%
a knight believed he
was purifying himself

00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:12.430 align:middle line:84%
of the corruption, temptation,
and superficialities

00:07:12.430 --> 00:07:13.740 align:middle line:90%
of the transitory world.

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:16.970 align:middle line:90%


00:07:16.970 --> 00:07:20.050 align:middle line:84%
As such, he was to lead
a hardworking, sober life

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:22.730 align:middle line:84%
of sacrifice,
dedication, and humility.

00:07:22.730 --> 00:07:27.070 align:middle line:90%


00:07:27.070 --> 00:07:30.110 align:middle line:84%
For humility is the
guardian of all virtues,

00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:32.935 align:middle line:84%
but few people ever saw much
humility in the Templars.

00:07:32.935 --> 00:07:37.840 align:middle line:90%


00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:40.010 align:middle line:84%
As individuals, the
Templars stood apart

00:07:40.010 --> 00:07:42.630 align:middle line:84%
with their white
robes and red cross.

00:07:42.630 --> 00:07:45.990 align:middle line:84%
As an organization, the Order
of the Temple of Solomon

00:07:45.990 --> 00:07:47.185 align:middle line:90%
prized its independence.

00:07:47.185 --> 00:07:48.550 align:middle line:90%


00:07:48.550 --> 00:07:51.210 align:middle line:84%
Templar castles ruled
their surrounding areas

00:07:51.210 --> 00:07:53.020 align:middle line:90%
with complete automony.

00:07:53.020 --> 00:07:55.340 align:middle line:84%
They brought little or no
interference from the king.

00:07:55.340 --> 00:07:58.400 align:middle line:90%


00:07:58.400 --> 00:08:01.510 align:middle line:84%
The temple often pursued
its own strategies,

00:08:01.510 --> 00:08:05.000 align:middle line:84%
even in direct opposition to
the overall Crusader policy.

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:22.510 align:middle line:90%


00:08:22.510 --> 00:08:25.530 align:middle line:10%
Early in the 13th century,
the Christian enclave

00:08:25.530 --> 00:08:28.910 align:middle line:10%
in the Holy Land stretched
from Antioch to Arsur,

00:08:28.910 --> 00:08:31.500 align:middle line:10%
and the Templars now
controlled a major proportion

00:08:31.500 --> 00:08:35.210 align:middle line:10%
of this from their castles
at Atlit, Chastel Blanc,

00:08:35.210 --> 00:08:36.860 align:middle line:10%
and in the mountains
around Antioc.

00:08:36.860 --> 00:08:40.789 align:middle line:90%


00:08:40.789 --> 00:08:43.360 align:middle line:84%
The undying aim of
all the Crusaders

00:08:43.360 --> 00:08:45.790 align:middle line:84%
remained the capture of
Jerusalem for Christianity.

00:08:45.790 --> 00:08:47.110 align:middle line:90%


00:08:47.110 --> 00:08:50.370 align:middle line:84%
The next opportunity arrived
at the Fifth Crusade,

00:08:50.370 --> 00:08:54.330 align:middle line:84%
whose leaders believed that the
only way to secure Jerusalem

00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:57.920 align:middle line:84%
was by first conquering
Egypt itself.

00:08:57.920 --> 00:09:01.180 align:middle line:84%
The Templars joined the Fifth
Crusade, whose objective

00:09:01.180 --> 00:09:03.408 align:middle line:90%
was Egypt's capital, Cairo.

00:09:03.408 --> 00:09:04.830 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.830 --> 00:09:07.970 align:middle line:84%
The city of Damietta
was the first obstacle

00:09:07.970 --> 00:09:08.885 align:middle line:90%
facing the Crusaders.

00:09:08.885 --> 00:09:14.590 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:18.550 align:middle line:84%
The Christian siege of
Damietta was long and bitter,

00:09:18.550 --> 00:09:21.760 align:middle line:84%
but finally, the Crusaders
overwhelmed the Muslims.

00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:24.130 align:middle line:10%
This so shocked
the Sultan of Egypt

00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:26.110 align:middle line:10%
that he immediately
offered to surrender

00:09:26.110 --> 00:09:29.570 align:middle line:10%
the Kingdom of Jerusalem if they
would return the captured city

00:09:29.570 --> 00:09:30.620 align:middle line:10%
and leave.

00:09:30.620 --> 00:09:32.220 align:middle line:90%
The Christians hesitated.

00:09:32.220 --> 00:09:33.910 align:middle line:90%


00:09:33.910 --> 00:09:35.800 align:middle line:84%
They were expecting
reinforcements

00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:39.140 align:middle line:84%
from Emperor Frederick II, who
had vowed to go on Crusade.

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:40.300 align:middle line:90%


00:09:40.300 --> 00:09:43.080 align:middle line:84%
If Frederick's forces
arrived in time,

00:09:43.080 --> 00:09:45.865 align:middle line:84%
Cairo itself would be
an attainable goal.

00:09:45.865 --> 00:09:53.960 align:middle line:90%


00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.720 align:middle line:84%
While the Christians
hesitated, the Muslims

00:09:56.720 --> 00:09:57.720 align:middle line:90%
prepared their defenses.

00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:59.010 align:middle line:90%


00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:01.690 align:middle line:84%
Twenty months after the
capture of Damietta,

00:10:01.690 --> 00:10:04.235 align:middle line:84%
the Fifth Crusade
finally headed south.

00:10:04.235 --> 00:10:07.720 align:middle line:84%
The Egyptians easily
cut their supply line

00:10:07.720 --> 00:10:09.500 align:middle line:90%
and flooded the valley.

00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:13.980 align:middle line:84%
The Christians accepted
the sultan's next offer--

00:10:13.980 --> 00:10:16.257 align:middle line:84%
they returned
Damietta and he let

00:10:16.257 --> 00:10:17.465 align:middle line:90%
them escape with their lives.

00:10:17.465 --> 00:10:27.680 align:middle line:90%


00:10:27.680 --> 00:10:31.360 align:middle line:84%
The failure of Emperor Frederick
II to arrive in the Holy Land

00:10:31.360 --> 00:10:33.940 align:middle line:84%
almost certainly resulted
in the destruction

00:10:33.940 --> 00:10:34.902 align:middle line:90%
of the Fifth Crusade.

00:10:34.902 --> 00:10:38.680 align:middle line:90%


00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:43.230 align:middle line:84%
>>Frederick eventually
went on crusade in 1228

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:46.190 align:middle line:84%
but was forced to turn
back because of illness,

00:10:46.190 --> 00:10:50.550 align:middle line:84%
and the papacy excommunicated
him as a result.

00:10:50.550 --> 00:10:51.870 align:middle line:90%


00:10:51.870 --> 00:10:56.420 align:middle line:84%
Frederick wasn't deterred by
this-- he then set out again,

00:10:56.420 --> 00:10:59.290 align:middle line:84%
but this very much
complicated his relations

00:10:59.290 --> 00:11:03.110 align:middle line:84%
with the powers that
already existed in Cyprus

00:11:03.110 --> 00:11:06.780 align:middle line:84%
and on the mainland
when he arrived there,

00:11:06.780 --> 00:11:08.870 align:middle line:84%
and it became rather
difficult for them

00:11:08.870 --> 00:11:12.890 align:middle line:84%
to have dealings with
him in the long term.

00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:19.010 align:middle line:84%
Moreover, Frederick expected
his own will to be obeyed.

00:11:19.010 --> 00:11:23.030 align:middle line:84%
He had a quasi absolutist regime
in the Kingdom of Sicily, which

00:11:23.030 --> 00:11:25.620 align:middle line:84%
was one of the important
parts of his empire,

00:11:25.620 --> 00:11:29.480 align:middle line:84%
and he found it
difficult to deal

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:33.360 align:middle line:84%
with military orders, accustomed
to being at least semi

00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:37.000 align:middle line:84%
independent, and a
Jerusalem baronage which

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:41.420 align:middle line:84%
had a very highly developed
sense of its legal rights.

00:11:41.420 --> 00:11:44.640 align:middle line:84%
So from the very
beginning, Frederick

00:11:44.640 --> 00:11:48.639 align:middle line:84%
was in conflict with
important powers in the east,

00:11:48.639 --> 00:11:49.930 align:middle line:90%
and this included the Templars.

00:11:49.930 --> 00:11:52.930 align:middle line:90%


00:11:52.930 --> 00:11:54.910 align:middle line:84%
>>As an order of
the Catholic Church,

00:11:54.910 --> 00:11:57.050 align:middle line:84%
the Templars were not
supposed to have dealings

00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.390 align:middle line:84%
with the excommunicated
Frederick,

00:11:59.390 --> 00:12:01.400 align:middle line:84%
but their conflict
with the German emperor

00:12:01.400 --> 00:12:02.824 align:middle line:90%
had begun much earlier.

00:12:02.824 --> 00:12:05.490 align:middle line:90%


00:12:05.490 --> 00:12:08.070 align:middle line:84%
Back in Europe,
Frederick had angrily

00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:11.080 align:middle line:84%
complained that the Templar
network had purchased so much

00:12:11.080 --> 00:12:12.930 align:middle line:84%
of his lands in
Italy that it was

00:12:12.930 --> 00:12:15.180 align:middle line:84%
trying to control
his entire kingdom.

00:12:15.180 --> 00:12:17.810 align:middle line:90%


00:12:17.810 --> 00:12:20.800 align:middle line:10%
After quarreling with the
Crusaders in the east,

00:12:20.800 --> 00:12:22.750 align:middle line:10%
Frederick II headed
down the coast

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:25.590 align:middle line:10%
and actually met with
the Sultan of Egypt.

00:12:25.590 --> 00:12:29.500 align:middle line:84%
At the city of Jaffa, he
signed a sensational treaty.

00:12:29.500 --> 00:12:32.820 align:middle line:84%
The Egyptians voluntarily
ceded back part of the Kingdom

00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:36.500 align:middle line:84%
of Jerusalem, including the Holy
City itself, to the Christians.

00:12:36.500 --> 00:12:37.590 align:middle line:90%


00:12:37.590 --> 00:12:40.950 align:middle line:84%
Almost single handedly,
and without bloodshed,

00:12:40.950 --> 00:12:43.940 align:middle line:84%
the excommunicate German
emperor had finally

00:12:43.940 --> 00:12:45.650 align:middle line:84%
recovered Jerusalem
for Christianity.

00:12:45.650 --> 00:12:48.040 align:middle line:90%


00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:51.210 align:middle line:84%
Frederick then went to the
Church of the Holy Sepulchre

00:12:51.210 --> 00:12:52.542 align:middle line:90%
and had himself crowned.

00:12:52.542 --> 00:13:00.910 align:middle line:90%


00:13:00.910 --> 00:13:04.460 align:middle line:84%
The Christians resident in the
west, especially the Templars,

00:13:04.460 --> 00:13:07.110 align:middle line:84%
were not impressed with
Frederick's achievement,

00:13:07.110 --> 00:13:08.670 align:middle line:84%
as one of the
clauses of the treaty

00:13:08.670 --> 00:13:11.140 align:middle line:84%
prevented the repair
of any fortifications

